<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,343,898,924]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Etymology:</emphasis>
The species is named in honor of Prof. Dr. Muhlis Özkan in appreciation of his studies of Turkish water mites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1223]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,345,973,999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Discussion:</emphasis>
Due to the absence of glandularia on Cx-III and the shape of the palp combining a P- 
<number box="[1422,1437,973,999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
bearing a finger-like ventrodistal extension and a P- 
<number box="[770,785,1010,1036]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="4.0">4</number>
with the two well developed ventral tubercles close to each other, bearing peg-like and truncated setae, 
<taxonomicName box="[761,979,1048,1073]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oezkani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[761,979,1048,1073]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Sperchon oezkani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[988,1087,1047,1073]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[988,1087,1047,1073]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicName box="[1322,1437,1048,1073]" class="Arachnida" family="Sperchonidae" genus="Sperchon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Sperchon</taxonomicName>
afzalipouri
</emphasis>
Bader &amp; Sepasgozarian, 
<number box="[591,654,1085,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1980.0">1980</number>
, described from 
<collectingCountry box="[856,904,1085,1111]" name="Iran" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bader" box="[920,1291,1085,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" refString="Bader, C. &amp; Sepasgozarian, H. (1980 a) Wassermilben (Acari, Prostigmata, Hydrachnellae) aus dem Iran. 11. Mitteilung. Sperchon (Mixosperchon) afzalipouri nov. spec. Journal of Entomological Society of Iran, 5 (1,2), 35 - 55." type="journal article" year="1980" yearSuffix="a">
Bader &amp; Sepasgozarian 
<number box="[1214,1277,1085,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="1980.0">1980</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic" pageId="3" pageNumber="46" refString="Pesic, V., Saboori, A., Asadi, M. &amp; Vafaei, R. (2004) New records of water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) from Iran, with the description of one new species. Zoology in the Middle East, 32, 97 - 110." type="journal article" year="2004">
Pešić 
<emphasis box="[1375,1428,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[151,215,1122,1148]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This species differs in having the ventral tubercles on P- 
<number box="[908,922,1122,1148]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="4.0">4</number>
closer to each other and a more elongated, finger-shaped distoventral projection of P- 
<number box="[648,662,1160,1186]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="2.0">2</number>
(compare 
<figureCitation box="[788,922,1160,1186]" captionStart="FIGURE 3 A – G. A – D" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[192,1423,231,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1424,194,1940]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – G. A – D. Sperchon oezkani sp. nov. (A – B, D = male, C = female): A = palp, laterall view; B – C = palp, medial view; D = IV-Leg- 4 – 6. E – G Sperchon afzalipouri Bader &amp; Sepasgozarian (E – F = male, G = female): E = palp, lateral view; F = palp, medial view; G = P- 4. Scale bars = 100 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196105/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
Figs. 
<number box="[853,866,1160,1186]" pageId="3" pageNumber="38" value="3.0">3</number>
A–C
</figureCitation>
with 
<figureCitation box="[990,1128,1160,1186]" captionStart="FIGURE 3 A – G. A – D" captionStartId="5.[151,256,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[192,1423,231,1927]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[176,1424,194,1940]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3 A – G. A – D. Sperchon oezkani sp. nov. (A – B, D = male, C = female): A = palp, laterall view; B – C = palp, medial view; D = IV-Leg- 4 – 6. E – G Sperchon afzalipouri Bader &amp; Sepasgozarian (E – F = male, G = female): E = palp, lateral view; F = palp, medial view; G = P- 4. Scale bars = 100 μm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/196105/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="38">
